# CXErrorCodeNotificationServiceExtensionError.Code.invalidClientProcess

**Case**

An error indicating that an invalid client process reported the incoming call.

## Declaration

```swift
case invalidClientProcess
```

## Discussion

Only call the [doc://com.apple.callkit/documentation/CallKit/CXProvider/reportNewIncomingVoIPPushPayload(_:completion:)] method from a [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UserNotifications/UNNotificationServiceExtension] object that is responding to an incoming notification request.

## Error Codes

- **CXErrorCodeNotificationServiceExtensionError.Code.missingNotificationFilteringEntitlement**: An error indicating that the notification service extension is missing the required filtering entitlement.
- **CXErrorCodeNotificationServiceExtensionError.Code.unknown**: An error that occurs when there is an unknown problem.
